<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1601,1987]" box="[199,1017,1673,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1673,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description.</emphasis>
For the species description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Shakhovskoy, I. B. &amp; Parin, N. V." box="[701,1014,1673,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="559 - 579" refId="ref87084" refString="Shakhovskoy, I. B. &amp; Parin, N. V. (2010) A comparative description and distribution of the flying fishes - Cypselurus poecilopterus, C. simus, and C. callopterus, sorted out into the species group of spotwing species of the subgenus Poecilocypselurus. Voprosy Ikhtiologii, 50 (5), 581 - 602. [in Russian, English translation in Journal of Ichthyology, 50 (8), 559 - 579] https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0032945210080011" type="journal article" year="2010">Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin 2010</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1601,1987]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,470,1709,1735]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Comparative remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[476,733,1709,1735]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="callopterus">
<emphasis box="[476,733,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cypselurus callopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most readily distinguished from all other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1838" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(except 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[281,376,1745,1771]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simus">
<emphasis box="[281,376,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. simus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[428,611,1745,1771]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poecilopterus">
<emphasis box="[428,611,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. poecilopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in its characteristic spotted pigmentation of the pectoral fins. Two species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[295,440,1781,1807]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,440,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cheilopogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jenkins" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[456,609,1781,1807]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrisignis">
<emphasis box="[456,609,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ch. atrisignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin" authorityYear="1961" box="[664,870,1781,1807]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rapanouiensis">
<emphasis box="[664,870,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ch. rapanouiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), distributed in Eastern Pacific, also have spots on the pectoral fins and may be confused with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[638,797,1817,1843]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="callopterus">
<emphasis box="[638,797,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. callopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These species may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1278,1436,1817,1843]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="callopterus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. callopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by longer lower jaw, usually projecting ahead of upper jaw (which is usually pointed anteriorly vs. roundish in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="callopterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. callopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the absence of true tricuspid jaw teeth and more anal-fin rays and vertebrae. Pectoral fin spots in these species are usually not as large and numerous as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[733,892,1925,1951]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="callopterus">
<emphasis box="[733,892,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. callopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and rather randomly spaced instead of being arranged in oblique rows. Juveniles of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jenkins" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[564,717,1961,1987]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrisignis">
<emphasis box="[564,717,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ch. atrisignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
